Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.41,0:08:15.67,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,From an old cement firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.67,0:08:18.93,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,They went bankrupt long ago and now it's unoccupied.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.72,0:08:24.02,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,In this lonesome mountain recess, there are remains of an empty quarry?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.17,0:08:27.02,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.36,0:08:32.03,Rika,Rika,0000,0000,0000,,No. The quarry isn't a place good kids should go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.44,0:08:39.53,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Even on our summer vacation leaflet, it said don't go near the quarry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.72,0:08:46.04,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,When you say it like that, any man would want to sneak in even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.60,0:08:51.87,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe there's a treasure heap as big as the one at the Dam Management site!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.90,0:08:57.09,Rena,Rena,0000,0000,0000,,A new treasure mound! Then I want to go too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.36,0:09:02.70,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,I don't recommend it. They say there's a 'hole' there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.70,0:09:04.81,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Hole? What do you mean by hole?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.09,0:09:08.05,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,I've also heard stories about the 'hole.'
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.69,0:09:10.57,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,But are they true?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.65,0:09:15.57,Rika,Rika,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's better that you don't approach the 'hole.'
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.88,0:09:19.49,Rena,Rena,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what it is… Mii-chan, what is this 'hole?'
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.49,0:09:23.23,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that's right. This isn't a story Kei-chan and Rena would know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.39,0:09:27.92,Rika,Rika,0000,0000,0000,,They say two people died.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.40,0:09:31.85,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bit of a ghost story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.85,0:09:32.92,Rena,Rena,0000,0000,0000,,A ghost story?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.22,0:09:36.87,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,I still remember it quite well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.87,0:09:41.93,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Especially since it could have been me who slipped inside the 'hole.'
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.03,0:09:45.48,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,There are times when I get really scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.81,0:09:47.28,Rena,Rena,0000,0000,0000,,You, Mii-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.28,0:09:48.22,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,{yes…}{we MAY want to keep ths for the sake of randomness, but atm I say we drop it. -R}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.78,0:09:52.65,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,I think that was about six or seven years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.65,0:09:55.02,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,It was when the Dam War was still peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.22,0:10:01.45,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,The kids were like the ones now in Hinamizawa, playing in the fields and the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.57,0:10:06.61,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,It was about then that the company owning the quarry collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.61,0:10:12.32,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,The good natured president of the company was tricked into co-signing the debt of the employees, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.32,0:10:15.51,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,They suddenly all absconded.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.51,0:10:20.35,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,If I recall, the president committed a double murder-suicide, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.35,0:10:21.72,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah… {\alphaH&FF&}with his wife and young child.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.72,0:10:24.20,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah… with his wife and young child.{wtf is this chris benoit?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.20,0:10:27.07,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,He killed both of them at the quarry's prefab office tent,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.07,0:10:31.10,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,and then poured lamp oil over himself and barbequed himself alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.27,0:10:37.03,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,{Huh, }Wait. Didn't Rika-chan say two people died?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.39,0:10:40.54,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,In that story, three people died.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.54,0:10:42.53,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, my bad, my bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.87,0:10:45.86,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Those three don't count towards the 'hole' story.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.57,0:10:51.50,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,But because of this suicide, the quarry was closed down and became unoccupied.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.88,0:10:58.01,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,And then the rumours that the suffering ghost of the president still wandered around the area of the incident began.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.40,0:11:02.51,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,That type of story attracts the curiosity of children, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.89,0:11:04.55,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it certainly does.{changing true to it certainly is - G}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.81,0:11:09.63,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,So we started thinking, "let's go there to play!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.63,0:11:10.52,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Has everyone gone there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.67,0:11:13.86,Rika,Rika,0000,0000,0000,,I never have.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.86,0:11:16.52,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,We were still very little then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.05,0:11:22.53,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,With that random bit of curiosity, \Nwe decided to play Kick the Can there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.51,0:11:26.24,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,No one seemed to care, but {\alphaH&FF&}there was this strange odour ever since we stepped foot in the quarry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.24,0:11:29.99,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,No one seemed to care, but there was this strange odour ever since we stepped foot in the quarry. {*considers leading this out to the scene change* -R}{btw odour is queen's english :P - G}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.00,0:11:32.83,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,It stinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.88,0:11:35.38,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Odour?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.38,0:11:37.59,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, how should I explain it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.10,0:11:40.92,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,It was like the smell of a rotten egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.92,0:11:43.52,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Like a rotten egg…? {\alphaH&FF&}Like sulfur?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.52,0:11:44.99,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Like a rotten egg…? Like sulfur?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.99,0:11:46.60,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah. Like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.91,0:11:50.86,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,But sulfur... that's usually emited near volanoes, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.86,0:11:52.89,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Is that something you'd smell in a quarry?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.89,0:11:54.15,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Don't know…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.94,0:12:00.07,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,But we soon stopped noticing it, and continued to play Kick the Can.{not gonna split this -R}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.45,0:12:03.08,Misc,Boy-01,0000,0000,0000,,Found you, Takashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.63,0:12:08.13,Misc,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,He found you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.28,0:12:16.17,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Then all of a sudden, out of nowhere, a person who... looked like a worker there charged at us.{this sounds so...suspicious, with the sulfuric scent and all - G}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.17,0:12:19.67,Misc,Ootori,0000,0000,0000,,You brats! This isn't a playground!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.07,0:12:21.97,Misc,Ootori,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.20,0:12:29.60,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,In the end we all ran away from there and called it a day…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.68,0:12:34.85,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,What? Don't tell me that's the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.00,0:12:37.36,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,It's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.52,0:12:39.86,Rena,Rena,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Mii-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.27,0:12:46.61,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,There was a boy{alpha here? - G} who didn't come home no matter how late it got.{hueg space is hueg, any way to split this? -R}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.69,0:12:49.33,Rena,Rena,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't come home…?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.26,0:12:55.15,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,When that man scolded us, we all panicked and ran home separately so we didn't know, but…{I don't really want to lead this one out, and I realize ending it right here is a bit short but... I prefer it over the other option. -R}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.37,0:13:00.65,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,He probably… had already disappeared at that time.{don't want to split this. I'd like to have it change to "But I think he had already vanished at that point.." or so. -R}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.65,0:13:01.59,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.58,0:13:06.99,Rika,Rika,0000,0000,0000,,He met with Oyashiro-sama's Curse and was Onikakushi'd,{not sure about met...tlc? - G}{yes, that's literally what it says お社様の祟りに遭って}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.99,0:13:08.97,Rika,Rika,0000,0000,0000,,is what they say.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.87,0:13:11.17,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Onikakushi?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.04,0:13:14.98,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,It's another ghost story of Hinamizawa.{not a direct TL}{rearranging - G}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.71,0:13:17.73,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,A ghost story… huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.73,0:13:18.44,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.33,0:13:23.44,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,His parents called everyone's houses, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.19,0:13:29.31,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,None of the children had returned together with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.31,0:13:30.99,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,And… what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.03,0:13:39.46,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,The father thought that he might have possibly gotten into an accident on his way back alone, so he drove to the quarry…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.53,0:13:42.05,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,And… was the boy found?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.67,0:13:45.84,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than being found…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.05,0:13:48.84,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,the father didn't come back either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.30,0:13:59.35,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,If I recall, the car was found by the river banks in Yagouchi on the path towards Hinamizawa, with both of their bodies inside.{I don't hear her mentioning anything about their bodies...? -R}{確か、父親とその子を載せた車がヤゴウチからヒナミザワへの戻る途中の沢で見つけたんでしたわね？ it doesn't say /bodies/ but it says they were both in the car, and it's obv. strongly implied}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.17,0:14:10.24,Rena,Rena,0000,0000,0000,,That's a sad story. When the father finally found him and they were on their way back home...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.24,0:14:13.91,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,This is where the story gets strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.38,0:14:18.75,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,It seems the scene of the accident is pretty close to the quarry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.41,0:14:22.38,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it strange for the scene of the accident to be close to the quarry?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.94,0:14:28.74,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,Because, it was quite late when the father went looking for him by car.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.74,0:14:31.43,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,To the point where the surrounding area would be pitch black.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.76,0:14:36.22,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,That would mean the boy stayed at the quarry until then.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.15,0:14:41.23,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he was caught by that worker man and was being scolded?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.11,0:14:46.09,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,About that… The police looked into it, {\alphaH&FF&}and they said there wasn't anyone at the quarry that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.09,0:14:49.28,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,About that… The police looked into it, and they said there wasn't anyone at the quarry that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.68,0:14:53.85,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.85,0:14:57.25,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,There was no doubt a strange{lit: scary, huge} man did chase us out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.89,0:14:59.54,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.66,0:15:07.17,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,And now there's the rumour that maybe that worker was a ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.17,0:15:12.39,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be. There's no ghost that makes that much noise as they run heavily!{blah, I don't like this either but it makes more sense at least... she's basically saying "There's no ghost who runs with a 'dotadota' (noise of heavy feet), and heavy like that!", maybe play with this a bit in editing -bd}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.27,0:15:16.57,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Putting the identity of that man aside…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.57,0:15:22.40,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,What I don't get is why the kid stayed at the quarry until dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.21,0:15:27.40,Rika,Rika,0000,0000,0000,,The rumour is that maybe he fell into the 'hole.'
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.67,0:15:29.05,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,'Hole?'
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.05,0:15:32.91,Rena,Rena,0000,0000,0000,,We returned back to the 'hole' again, but what is this 'hole?'
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.40,0:15:36.73,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,It's a 'hole!' A very deep one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.73,0:15:41.41,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,They say it's so deep that it goes to the depths of the earth and connects to the kingdom of Demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.94,0:15:47.01,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,In the lore of Onigafuchi, it's said that beneath the village is the kingdom of Demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.01,0:15:49.71,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning Hell is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.30,0:15:54.09,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,And it was suggested that maybe there's a hole there that connects the two worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.44,0:15:56.42,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,I see. {\alphaH&FF&}That's why it's called Onikakushi, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.42,0:15:58.90,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That's why it's called Onikakushi, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.90,0:16:05.61,Rena,Rena,0000,0000,0000,,But that kid couldn't have vanished, right?{split?} He was able to meet with his father and was in an accident afterwards, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.84,0:16:12.32,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I say this at the beginning, that there was a sulfuric odour in the quarry that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.70,0:16:18.77,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that when the first person to find the car peered into the vehicle,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.77,0:16:22.27,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,he smelled a slight odour of rotten eggs from inside the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.80,0:16:25.88,Rena,Rena,0000,0000,0000,,The sulfuric odour!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.42,0:16:29.84,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,The smell of sulfur isn't normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.04,0:16:35.58,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it called hydrogen sulfide, the poisonous gas that reeks with a sulfuric odour?{K1, Higu gang. you people are too smart. possibly too smart for your own good. -R}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.38,0:16:42.60,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Every so often, there are stories on the news about workers getting poisoned while cleaning an industrial liquid waste tank, right?{adding while there - G}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.73,0:16:48.71,Rena,Rena,0000,0000,0000,,So maybe there was a tank like that at the quarry, and there was a crack which leaked out the bad gas?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.71,0:16:52.27,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, then the story would make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.88,0:17:02.12,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,While he was playing Kick the Can, he walked into a bad area, and breathed in the awful gas from the waste tanks and fell unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.45,0:17:09.37,Rika,Rika,0000,0000,0000,,And when the father found him, he must have also breathed in the bad gas.{changing while to when - G}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.40,0:17:18.19,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,I see. If you explain it that way, it clears up this old mystery easily.{not a direct tl}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.85,0:17:22.40,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there's no way to know the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.40,0:17:29.62,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,but even so, I think there's something lurking underneath it all that makes this accident not just any accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.45,0:17:36.99,Rika,Rika,0000,0000,0000,,If it wasn't just any accident, then what do you think is lurking underneath?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.99,0:17:38.49,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Hmmm, let's see…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.02,0:17:40.79,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,There are several things that stand out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.79,0:17:43.04,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,The worker who shouldn't have been there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.04,0:17:45.83,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,The reason the boy stayed at the quarry until dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.83,0:17:49.67,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,And then the bizarre death in the car.{removing the as from as in the car - G}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.48,0:17:55.42,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if we go to the quarry, we can find out whether or not there really is a dangerous gas leak.{Well, if we go to the quarry, we can see if there really is a dangerous gas leak.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.05,0:17:59.58,Keiichi,Keiichi,0000,0000,0000,,Mion, don't tell me you're actually thinking of going.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.58,0:18:05.27,Satoko,Satoko,0000,0000,0000,,If that is true, then the quarry is a dangerous place even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.74,0:18:09.98,Rena,Rena,0000,0000,0000,,I don't agree to going to such a place, I guess…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.36,0:18:13.70,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's now piqued my interest.{How do you guys want to handle the ojisan?}{I'll bump in here... Guesstimate, but doesn't she say "On the contrary, I'm interested (no, not that kind of interested dammit)in that old man..." "sparked my interest" is a better way of putting it, but she is definitively talking about the old guy. So the proper tl would be a mix of the one L_E ended with, and the one he added as a comment -R}{No, I think she's referring to herself with oji-san. Even in onikakushi (the game version), keiichi mentions that mion has a bit of an oji-san side to her every now and again :) -bd}{Yes, this is a "me" Oji-san not a "him" Oji-san. <3 Mion. - C}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.96,0:18:19.99,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,After listening to Kei-chan's theory, I feel like I could see the truth behind this ghost story.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.62,0:18:23.58,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Kei-chan, aren't you interested?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.58,0:18:25.96,Mion/Shion,Mion,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you want to know the real truth?
